# Docs Are HTML Canonical

- Create and update repository documentation under `docs/` as self-contained `*.html` files.
- Do not create new `docs/*.md` files unless the user explicitly asks for a temporary draft.
- When replacing old Markdown docs, update repository links to point to the matching `.html` file.
- Keep docs self-contained for offline use: no CDN scripts, remote fonts, remote images, or online assets.
- Mermaid or diagram source may be embedded in HTML as `<pre class="mermaid">` when no offline renderer is available.
